🌾 IoT in Smart Agriculture
📌 Overview

This project is a detailed report on the application of the Internet of Things (IoT) in agriculture. It explains how modern farming techniques use smart devices and data analytics to improve productivity and sustainability.

🎯 Objective

To study the role of IoT in agriculture

To understand smart farming techniques

To analyze real-world applications

🔍 Key Topics Covered

Smart irrigation systems

Soil moisture monitoring

Crop health analysis

Weather monitoring

IoT architecture in agriculture

⚙️ Technologies Used

IoT Sensors

Cloud Computing

Data Analytics

🌐 Applications

Precision farming

Automated irrigation

Smart greenhouse systems

📊 Outcome

This project provides a clear understanding of how IoT improves efficiency, reduces resource wastage, and supports sustainable agriculture.

📚 Conclusion

IoT is transforming traditional agriculture into smart farming, helping farmers make better decisions and increase crop yield.
